Ramsay, aged 53, died after a fall during the annual Passion for Speed International Historic race earlier this month. CAPE TOWN - Details around a fatal motorcycle accident at the Killarney International Raceway are expected by next week.Gavin Ramsay, aged 53, died after a fall during the annual Passion for Speed International Historic race earlier this month.Officials say video evidence of the crash also formed part of an investigation.Killarney management has confirmed an investigation was launched shortly after the East Rand motorcycle champion's crash.His death caused an outcry on social media with claims that basic racing control regulations were flouted during the race.Circuit manager Des Easom disagrees. At this point the investigation has not revealed any areas where proper procedures were not followed. He says investigators have considered input from fellow competitors, spectators and racing officials.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)